{ This is by far the most popular move, completing the development of the four Knights. The alternatives are less reliable for Black and give White an edge without any particular problems. One move that Black plays sometimes is  3...g6  , after which we reply  4.d4  in the spirit of our repertoire. After  4...exd4  5.Nxd4  we will very likely transpose to line #4,  which we checked in this Quickstarter guide via the move order 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6. White is better with the standard attacking setup of Be3/f3/O-O-O. }
4. d4
