{ Black now has three basic approaches. He needs to develop the f8-Bishop soon, so the first two approaches are to play 6... e6 or 6... g6 now or after inserting 6... Nc6 7. d4 cxd4 8. Nxd4. The third approach is to try some concrete play after 6... Nc6, based on the Queen sortie ...Qd7-g4 !? to attack the still unprotected g-pawn. This ...Qg4 idea is rare and examined in the dedicated chapter, but not analysed in the Quickstarter. }
6... g6 7. d4 cxd4 8. Nxd4 Nc6
