4... Bd6 { This is one of Black's tries to reach the Ne7/Bf5 trade. } 5. c4 Nf6
{ Probably the most natural move. You will also encounter  5...Ne7 ??  , which allows  6.c5  , winning the Bishop. }
6. Nc3 dxc4 7. Bxc4
{ This position is very similar to 5. c4 dxc4 6. Bxc4 Nf6 when I recommend 7. Qe2+ !. If White plays 7. Nc3 instead we would reach exactly the same situation here. So in some way 5... Nf6 6. Nc3 is a more precise move order by Black. That being said, White still has chances to play for an advantage. }
