9. h3
{ This is a very useful move, preventing Bg4, now that White can no longer answer Bg4 with the mechanism of h3/g4/Ne5 due to Black's increased control over e5, after he played Nc6. }
9... h6 { Black also fears Bg5, so he answers in symmetrical fashion. } 10. Qc2
{ I think this is interesting because of the attacking ideas shown below. The lines after 10. Qc2 go exceptionally deep for this repertoire, but they were interesting to explore, so I decided to include them. Again, if you don't feel like going there:   10.Re1  or any other active move is fine. }
