{ This normal looking move allows White to realize his attacking idea connected to Qc2. Instead   11...Be6  stops the sacrifice at the cost of some structural damage. }
12. Bxh6
{ Computers evaluate this as equal at the end, but White has all the fun. }
12... gxh6 13. Qg6+ Kh8 14. Qxh6+ Nh7 15. Ne4 Be7 16. Ne5
{ Black is under huge pressure. Engines find their way around this, but it is very unpleasant for humans to play Black. }
