{ This is the 'Modern Defence'. I always felt this is one of the weirdest opening names. Will it still be called like that in 50 years time ? Anyway, let's look at the actual moves.The main difference between this opening and the Pirc Defence is that Black does not put his Knight on f6 early on. This makes a difference in many ways. One important point is that White is not able to operate with an early Be3/Qd2/Bh6 manoeuver. Black also retains the option of developing the Knight to e7, or even h6 in some cases. The downside of Black's game is clearly the lack of development and neglect of central control.Against the Modern, we will opt for a similar setup as against the Pirc. Note that whenever Black plays Nf6 in the next few moves we will transpose to the Pirc. }
