5. c4
{ Now that Black has moved the Bishop already, a Bb4 setup will lose a full tempo in a wide-open position. }
5... Nf6 6. Nc3 O-O
{ A clever move order by Black.   Now simply going  7.Bd3  leads nowhere, so White is more or less forced to take on  d5.   7.c5  is playable by the way, but I don't like to advance while still being underdeveloped.  7 cxd5 also does not develop immediately, but it frees c4 for the Bishop and Black will have to spend time getting the pawn back. }
