10... Nb6 11. Bb3 a5 12. Ne5 { An important idea to remember. } 12... Bxe5 13.
dxe5 Rxe5 14. a4
{ After the coming Bf4, White will be better due to his Bishop pair and space advantage. Note that Qd4 is an important idea as well. }
14... Nbxd5 { Of course, we have to check this. } 15. Nxd5 Nxd5 16. f4 Rf5 17.
g4 { And White wins. } *

