{ By far the most popular move and recommended by John Bartholomew in his Chessable repertoire. }
11. Ne2
{ Avoiding trades after Ne4. The Knight might prove useful on g3 or f4 later. }
11... Nd5 12. Qg3 { This attacks g7 and prepares Bg5 if appropiate. } 12... g6
{ This is best way to deal with the threat against the g7 pawn. } 13. Bh6
{ We stop Black going O-O and preserve the Bishop from a possible trade against the Knight on d5. }
13... b5 { John's recommendation for Black. it is better than Bf8 for sure. }
14. h4 Bf8
