6. Nc3
{ Our setup includes Nc3/ Bd3/Nge2. The main point of this setup is to make the Black c8 Bishop look a bit silly. Black usually tries to pin the f3 Knight by Bg4, so we avoid Nf3 completely. The Nge2 based setup has some more concrete ideas that we will investigate now. }
6... Nc6
{ Black is putting some pressure on d4, so Bd3 is not possible now. This move still has little independent value, if we similarly play to the main line Be7. }
7. Be3
{ Instead  7.d5  is a try to punish Black, but it is not much better than just this natural move that will transpose to ...Be7, most likely. }
7... Bf5 8. Bd3
