15... Qb8
{ 15...c5  A principled move, but Black's pawn structure remains vulnerable.  16.c3  This is not the only option of course, but I like the regrouping illustrated by the following line.  Re8  17.Qd2  a5  It is not clear that this move is necessary, but Black has to watch out for b2-b4 and often prefers to make this harder to play for White.  18.Nf4  This was White's intention. The Knight looks at d5 and e6 now.  Bd7  19.Rxe8+  Bxe8  20.Be2  This Bishop is directed to f3, putting more pressure on the centre. White is still exerting some pressure while running no risks at all. }
