20... e5
{ 20...Qc7  21.dxe6  Rxe6  22.Rd5  is a possible line to illustrate the White rook on d5. There is pressure in this middlegame, but the endgames might be depressing for Black as well, with c5 and g7 being on dark squares. In the game Black decides to close everything down, but giving White a protected passed pawn is a concession. }
21. f4
