{ 17.Bc2  was fine as well. One idea is to direct this Bishop against d5. In the game White goes for a2-a3, followed by Bb1 and a possible Ba2 later. Bc2 is a bit quicker, but playing the pawn to a3 is useful to cover b4 and free up the Queen to move. The second plan to go for is to gain space on the Kingside with pushing the f and possibly g-pawn. }
17... Qd7
{ 17...Ne6  is also answered by  18.a3  This is very similar to 18... Ne6 below. }
